    • Constructor Detail

      • TestResult

        public TestResult(TestRun run,
                  boolean passed,
                  int failtype,
                  String message)
        The standard constructor. This constructor takes most of the arguments to specify the test result. The elapsed time and log file are set after creation.
        Parameters:
        run - the test description, configTag pair
        passed - the state of the status: failed=false, passed=true
        failtype - the failure type, ignored for a passed test
        message - a detail message for the test result
